OL,4,G2100FHow the Nazis Lost the War
OL,5,     GGermany had few allies before
OL,6,     GWWII, and, for various reasons,
OL,7,     Gthose alliances were doomed to
OL,8,     Gfail. Ultimately, Germany paid a
OL,9,     Gheavy price for the partnerships
OL,10,     Gthey forged with the Axis Powers.
OL,11,G2200FHow the Nazis Lost the War
OL,12,     GAs Germany's resources dwindled,
OL,13,     GHitler and Goebbels promoted
OL,14,     GWonder Weapons as a path to
OL,15,     Gvictory. However, this blind
OL,16,     Gbelief in technology became a
OL,17,     Gmajor hindrance to the Nazi war
OL,18,     Geffort.
